by Subaruchan192

The Apocalypse is on its peak and the Winchesters are trying to stop everything with Castiel’s help. One night, however, a young woman appears in front of them, who remembers nothing, but suddenly knows everything about them. The investigation showed, she is neither a demon, fallen angel nor any other mystical creature. The only thing they knew for sure, is that their names are engraved into her soul? Who is she and why was she brought to them?

~ * ~
Disclaimer: I’ve only been watching Supernatural until Season 8, so if anything in this story contradicts later events, please do not tell me;) Otherwise, I’d like to mention that I’m not going to include romance in this story, though because of the basis, it could often happen that way and it will be joked about. Otherwise, I wish you a lot of fun with this simple, little story.

This is a translation of my German fanfiction.

summary: talking the other day with a few people on discord, about crowley Falling and aziraphale not, and the assumption it’s tied to...
body:
talking the other day with a few people on discord, about crowley Falling and aziraphale not, and the assumption it’s tied to questioning and doubting god

“Are you saying,” said Crowley, “that He planned it this way all along? From the very beginning?”
Aziraphale conscientiously wiped the top of the bottle and passed it back. “Could have,” he said. “Could have. One could always ask Him, I suppose.”
“From what I remember,” replied Crowley, thoughtfully, “-and we were never actually on what you might call speaking terms-He wasn’t exactly one for a straight answer. In fact, in fact, he’d never answer at all. He’d just smile, as if He knew something that you didn’t.”
“And of course that’s true,” said the angel. “Otherwise, what’d be the point?”
There was a pause, and both beings stared reflectively off into the distance, as if they were remembering things that neither of them had thought of for a long time.

both of them have doubts and questions, only crowley is loud about it, and aziraphale isnt. crowley also appears to be fairly more social than aziraphale, somewhat more dependent on feedback and interaction.

He’d been an angel once. He hadn’t meant to Fall. He’d just hung around with the wrong people.

having questions on your own is one thing. hearing other people voice those same questions is another. it makes those questions louder, stronger, gives them support.

crowleys more social tendencies probably made him easier to find and recruit, and

Human beings mostly aren’t [evil]. They just get carried away by new ideas…

crowley and aziraphale are pretty damn human right from the start, and the rest of the angels and demons probably are somewhat along those lines too

title: Sanctuary
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2Dnkf4y

by AEpixie7

Crowley flees Europe during World War II. To Hawaii, at a REALLY bad time (poor unlucky bastard). Kushiel, the Angel of Punishment, assumes Pearl Harbor is Crowley’s doing, and attacks him, very nearly killing him. Crowley invokes his right to Sanctuary, which only a willing angel can grant outside of a church. Who do you think he calls?
